        introduction: "Milan, Italy's economic and cultural capital, is the most popular international destination for residents and visitors of the Principality of Monaco. Separated by 340 kilometres of motorway through some of Western Europe's most spectacular scenery, these two capitals of luxury and business share deep economic, cultural and social ties. The taxi journey from Monaco crosses the Italian Ligurian coast through Ventimiglia, San Remo and Savona before reaching the Po Valley and greater Milan. Milan captivates with its extraordinary artistic heritage — the Duomo, Leonardo da Vinci's Last Supper, the Brera Gallery — and its status as the world fashion capital with the Quadrilatero della Moda housing Versace, Prada, Armani and Dolce & Gabbana flagships. La Scala theatre, the Borsa Italiana and the modern Porta Nuova and CityLife districts complete the portrait of a city seamlessly blending tradition and modernity.",
        itineraire: "The journey from Monaco begins on the French A8 motorway, quickly reaching the Italian border at Ventimiglia. You then take the Autostrada dei Fiori (A10) along the Ligurian coast, alternating between spectacular tunnels and viaducts with plunging views of the Mediterranean. The motorway passes through Bordighera, San Remo — famous for its Italian song festival — Imperia and Savona. At Genoa, the route bypasses the city to the north and joins the A7 (Autostrada dei Giovi) which crosses the Ligurian Apennines. The descent to the Po Valley is swift through Tortona and Voghera to Milan's outskirts. Entry into Milan is via the Tangenziale Ovest or the urban motorway serving the city's various districts.",
        conseils: "For this 3h20 international journey, plan an early departure if you have a midday appointment in Milan. The driver can stop at an Italian rest area after about 1.5 hours for coffee or a break. Carry your ID — while the France-Italy border is open (Schengen area), spot checks may occur at Ventimiglia. Combined tolls (French and Italian) amount to about €35 and are included in the fare. Note Milan's ZTL (restricted traffic zones): the driver has the necessary permits to access regulated areas. If heading to Fiera di Milano or the Porta Nuova business district, specify this when booking.",
